Hebb 2021

Austin McCoy

March 17 2022

Loading the necessary packages

library(readxl)
library(hagis)
library(pander)

Loading in the data from Hebb et al 2021, (2016-2018 Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky and Ohio) manuscript

We will look at the data in this order: 1.) Illinois, 2) Indiana, 3) Kentucky and 4) Ohio

Illinois

final_data <- read_excel("pathotype surveys data.xlsx", 
    sheet = "Hebb 2021")


final_data_IL <- subset(final_data, state_prov =="Illinois")
final_data_IN <- subset(final_data, state_prov =="Indiana")
final_data_KY <- subset(final_data, state_prov =="Kentucky")
final_data_OH <- subset(final_data, state_prov =="Ohio")

Setting the hagis arguments - Illinois

hagis_args_IL <- list(
  x = final_data_IL,
  
  cutoff = 1, 
  
  control = "rps",
  
  sample = "Isolate",
  
  gene = "Rps",
  
  perc_susc = "Susceptible.1" 
  
)
